com.dukes.lang.parser.node

Class AbstractSyntaxNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dukes.lang.parser.node.AbstractSyntaxNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BodyNode, ExpressionNode, FormalNode, FunctionNode, PrintNode, ProgramNode

    public abstract class AbstractSyntaxNode
extends Object

    Represents an abstract syntax tree. This class is extended to allow the use of other programmers to make their own syntax.

    Since:
    0.2.0

      • dataAsString

        public String dataAsString()
        Returns specific data as a string representation. This can be used to print the tree very pretty. Each subclass should if possible override this method to return the string representations of each of it's data, separated by commas. Preferably, they should be enclosed with brackets.
        Returns:
        An empty string.

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns a string representation of this node. Does some pretty cool formatting, and assumes that the name of a subclass ends with "Node" and doesn't contain it anywhere else. To change how this is pretty printed, change the prettyPrint() method.
        Overrides:
